14 §3173-J. Rate-setting system for development and maintenance of sustainable,
15 efficient and value-oriented MaineCare payment models and rates
16 reimbursement of MaineCare-covered services
17 This section establishes a rate-setting system for the development and maintenance of
18 MaineCare payment models and rates reimbursement of MaineCare-covered services that
19 comply complies with the requirement in 42 United States Code, Section 1396a that rates
20 be consistent with efficiency, economy and quality of care; that are is adequate to support
21 MaineCare member access to services; and that are is equitable and data-driven.
22 1. Definitions. As used in this section, unless the context otherwise indicates, the
23 following terms have the following meanings.
24 A. "Alternative payment model" means a health care payment model that uses
25 financial incentives to promote or leverage greater value for patients, purchasers,
26 payers or providers and that connects at least a portion of reimbursement to
27 performance on defined quality measures.
28 B. "MaineCare section of policy" means a set of MaineCare-covered services, as
29 categorized by the department through the adoption of rules that specify the parameters
30 for coverage.
31 B-1. "Payment model" means the method that the department uses to reimburse
32 providers for health care services, including whether the reimbursement is paid on a
33 fee-for-service basis or another basis such as per member, per month or an estimated
34 basis that is cost settled.
35 C. "Rate determination" means a process conducted by the department to establish the
36 payment model, associated reimbursement rate methodology, base and, if applicable,
37 the rate amount or payment model for a MaineCare section of policy or for a specific
38 covered service, whether through adoption or adaptation of a benchmark rate or
39 payment model from another payer or development through a rate study.
40 D. "Rate study" means an analysis conducted by the department or its contracted
41 vendor to develop a recommended rate payment model, associated reimbursement
42 methodology and resulting base rate amount and payment model based on the service
