413 model and cost components for the service amounts for current or potential MaineCare-
424 covered services. A rate study relies on data collected as part of the analysis conducted
435 by the department to inform the cost of providing services and resulting rates rather
446 than relying on a benchmark of existing rates or payment models used by other payers.
5 E. "Reimbursement methodology" means the method for determining the rate or
6 reimbursement amount under the payment model. Examples of reimbursement
7 methodologies include using standardized assumptions for determining service cost
8 components, such as staffing levels, wages based on required qualifications, benefits
9 and program administration, to determine a reimbursement rate per unit of service;
10 using cost-based reimbursement, under which the MaineCare program determines the
11 percentage it will pay of reported allowable costs; and adjusting reimbursements for
12 patient acuity or the relative duration or intensity of the service.
13 2. Rate-setting system principles and processes. The department shall establish
14 MaineCare provider payment models, including reimbursement rates, including those paid
15 through fee-for-service and alternative payment models. The rates must be established
16 methodologies and rate amounts, where applicable, in accordance with the following
17 principles and processes and adopted through rulemaking as described in subsection 3.
18 Changes to rates required by the Federal Government to assist with emergency or
19 extraordinary circumstances or rate reductions required by the Legislature for the purpose
20 of responding to projected MaineCare budget shortfalls are not subject to this section. The
21 department shall:
22 A. Develop annually a schedule of rate determination by MaineCare section of policy
23 in consultation with the MaineCare Rate Reform Expert Technical Advisory Panel
24 established under subsection 5 as follows:
25 (1) Post the rate determination schedule on its publicly accessible website;
26 (2) Provide an opportunity for the public to review and comment on the rate
27 determination schedule and make available a summary of these comments on its
28 publicly accessible website; and
29 (3) Conduct off-schedule rate determinations as the department finds appropriate;
30 B. Conduct or contract for, every 4 years, a comprehensive benchmarking report to
31 compare MaineCare rates for all services to those paid by Medicare, at least 5
32 comparison Medicaid states and any appropriate Maine commercial payers. The
33 department shall provide public notice of the initiation of the comprehensive
34 benchmarking process, provide an opportunity for the public to review and comment
35 on the draft report and make available a summary of these comments alongside the
36 final report;
37 C. No less frequently than once every 5 years, conduct a rate determination process
38 for each MaineCare section of policy or for a specific covered service, in accordance
39 with the following procedures:
40 (1) Provide public notice of initiation of the rate determination for a MaineCare
41 section of policy or for a specific covered service;
42 (2) Consider and, when appropriate, adopt alternative payment models that use
43 financial incentives to promote or leverage greater value for the MaineCare
44 program. This consideration must include a review of research on any available
